, along with their beauty and the ethical problem of their violence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Okt 2022) 0aHuman body (Philosophy) 0aHuman body (Philosophy). 0aMartial artsxPhilosophy. 0aMind and body. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / Martial Arts & Self-Defense.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106658640 cprintz978023117272140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231539340423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231539340/original  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066586-4  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK